    "0 is used as the reference spectrum relative to which the differences of the wing-band mean fluxes of other spectra are calculated, it does not appear in the plots in Figure 17b.",
    "The consistency of the Hα profiles in the line wings is judged by the maximum absolute difference value of the wing-band mean fluxes (indicated by a circle symbol in Figure 17b).",
    "To determine the threshold of the maximum absolute difference of wing-band mean fluxe for recognizing the stellar sources with consistent Hα profiles in the line wings, we analyze the distribution of the maximum absolute difference values of the wingband mean fluxes for the stellar source sample after the screening conditions described in Sections 3.2.1 and 3.2.2.",
    "The histograms of the distribution are shown in Figure 17c and 17d, which use linear and logarithmic scales on their vertical axes, respectively.",
    "By carefully examining the distribution of the maximum absolute difference values of the wing-band mean fluxes and the associated spectral profiles, the upper threshold of the maximum absolute difference of wing-band mean flux for recognizing the consistent Hα profiles in the line wings is determined to be 0.022 (indicated with a horizontal dashed line in Figure 17b and a vertical dashed line in Figures 17c and 17d)."
